{
  "bio": [
    "Avram Glazer and his five siblings sold a quarter of their 68% stake in Manchester United to British chemicals billionaire Jim Ratcliffe in 2023.",
    "The deal valued the team at $5.4 billion (net of debt). Their father, shopping mall magnate Malcolm Glazer (d. 2014), bought the team for $1.4 billion in 2005.",
    "The Glazer siblings still own the NFL's Tampa Bay Buccaneers; their father acquired the franchise for $192 million in 1995, and it's now worth an estimated $6.6 billion.",
    "Avram co-chairs Man U with his brother Joel and has been Chairman of the Board of Innovate Corp since 2020.",
    "Avram holds a bachelor's degree in business administration from Washington University (St. Louis) and a law degree from American University."
